<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Validate_Float is returning some invalid validations.  For example, strings "74.8960196583719" and "169.76664148522" are evaluated as invalid.  See example below (first tests are for baseline and were taken from <a href="http://framework.zend.com/issues/browse/ZF-5879">ZF-5879</a>):</p>

<p>Tests:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;?php
require_once 'Zend/Validate.php';

$floats = array(// floats
                0.000000234,
                1.0000000234,
                0.000050004,
                0.005000004,
                // strings
                '0.000000234',
                '1.0000000234',
                '0.000050004',
                '0.005000004');

foreach ($floats as $f) {
    echo "$f: ";
    var_dump(Zend_Validate::is($f,'Float'));
}

echo "----------------------------------------------------------\n";

$floats = array(// floats
                74.8960196583719,
                169.76664148522,
                // strings
                '74.8960196583719',
                '169.76664148522');

foreach ($floats as $f) {
    echo "$f: ";
    var_dump(Zend_Validate::is($f,'Float'));
}</code></pre>

